cocaine (0.7.4-0) lucid; urgency=low

  * Core: proper fork() + exec() magic for slave spawning.
  * Core: pool grow control via the 'grow-threshold' variable.
  * Core: no more 'instances', nobody grasped the point of it anyway.
  * Core: much more granular exception control in the code, for better diagnostics.
  * Core: the reason for engine shutdown is now visible in the status response.
  * Core: loggers no longer parse messages if they're not going to be emitted
    because of the verbosity settings.
  * Core: worker i/o now supports timeouts.
  * Drivers: native server major speedup.
  * Python: acquire GIL only on method invocations, so that other Python threads
    could be spawned for some background idle processing tasks.
  * Python: read() now accepts the 'size' argument to read the request in
    chunks.
  * Python: i/o object now supports readline() method for additional WSGI
    compatibility.

 -- Andrey Sibiryov <kobolog@yandex-team.ru>  Thu, 19 Apr 2012 18:49:00 +0400

